values:
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It's going to be an exciting weekend. My best friend Erin and her friend Jae from Australia are coming to visit and on Sunday night we're going to the Cursive show at Webster Hall. It'll be great to see her because I miss her a lot plus I get to meet her cool friend with the cool accent.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I've been thinking lately that i want to cut my hair short again. it's grown out a bit to the flippies stage with the intention of letting it grow out even longer. now it just looks flat and lifeless. Combine that with the fact that it makes me look 15 and it's time to go with something nicer. I want to cut it myself like i usually do but I need help with cutting the back since i don't have a large enough mirror to see the back with. I want to get it cut somewhere in the city preferably. I'll&nbsp;have them use a razor and maybe have some European person do it. They always seem to know what looks cool.&nbsp;
I also need to buy some fitted blazers. i don't like the ones I find at the usual places. they always are cut more genrously and i don't want to look like a a college professor. So maybe this weekend i'll do a bit of shopping.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Finally got our internet up and running today. Apparently the fucker that was here last week fucked around with the wiring and in all that effort never managed to go outside to the box and switch our DSL on. Luckily today we had someone competent enough to realize that and repair it.&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp; I also want an Ipod. Probably will buy the nano since i wouldnt be able to fill up a 30 gigger. I'm also really impressed with the new Imacs that are out. They just installed some at school and i have to admit they're damn sexy.&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I'm also dually excited because i just did my degree audit for my current major which is Illustration and did a mock one for an Art and Design education degree.&nbsp;What i found is that i can switch to Art ed. and still only need the same amount of credits to graduate at the same time.&nbsp;even better, i won't have to continue taking these bullshit classes like the one i just complained about. Instea dI'll be taking education type coursework. Plus if i work my ass off i'll be able to graduate in the fall of 2008. if i take summer classes then it'll be even earlier&nbsp;in the spring 2008.&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp; 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I'm really considering buying a motor scooter to commute back and forth from school. I remember back in the 80's when I was really little, I had this babysitter named Sandra who dated this guy named "Fly" who'd come over to hang out with her while she baby sat us. He was a weasely looking fella' who bore a striking resemblance to Weird Al Yankovic, complete with the trademark mustache, hair,&nbsp;and glasses. Anyway, he'd always show up in this snazzy red scooter and if we begged him enough, he'd take use for a spin around the block on it.&nbsp; At 5 years old, I thought that was about the coolest thing in the world next to finding a M.A.S.K. hologram ring in a box of King Vitamin cereal.&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Anyhow, now that I've been riding around my bike to get to and from places here in Brooklyn I've been looking to alternative modes of transportation for when I'm feeling a bit lazy. Seeing as scooters are small enough to bring inside the apartment when not in use and the fact they often get 60-80 miles per gallon, I'd say it is a viable and economical solution to my growing reluctance to pedal my ass off to class every morning. They're also relatively cheap to buy and even cheaper to insure.&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Who knows, maybe I'll start a scooter riding chapter in Crown Heights. Whose with me?
